message:
hey! Can I ask - is there a way to disable our chat to be in the native language of users? As a result of it being in their native language - they also speak to us in their native language and expect we will also speak to them. Hey @Dimitris Nikolaou! Just want to make sure I understand this correctly. Is the use case that a customer is using something like Google Translate in their browser and it’s changing your messages to their language and they’re responding in kind and you’d like to disable Google Translate on the chat messages? hey @Dimitris Nikolaou just wanted to check if you saw @Jon OBryan message? Hey! Thanks for the follow up here. It is my understanding that the folks that have a different language to English set up, see our starting prompts in their own language - hence, they continue the conversation in that language when they want to ask the human operatior. Is this assumption of mine incorrect? You are 100% correct! This is done by browsers where user can set auto translation and whole page will be translated to their language. You can choose to disable this setting on your on your whole application or just for Atlas widget with in your application code, here is the documentation about this settings https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Global_attributes/translate Let me know if this works for you. Hey guys, coming back to this.I believe that it should not be the expected behaviour, even when using Google Translate for the rest of the page, for the chatbox to translate. We get 10% of our tickets in another language and it’s a friction point to respond.I think that the expected behaviour here should be for the chatbot to be in English and potentially have an option in user dashboard to enable google translate to impact the chatbox.Thanks! hey @Dimitris Nikolaou I going to check with our team and have an update for you on Monday — will try to see if their is a way to do so you don’t need to make any changes. offereing a quick way to translate the text from our users to English, so that we can understand, could also work. But if we responded in English, they would have to see in their language. This is what we see for reference and it’s just a friction point to respond. Can’t blame the customer for speaking to us in French, as they are prompted to do so. Hey Dimitris, we add a feature for you disable the auto translation. You can change your atlas start script and replace it with the followingwindow.Atlas.call('start', {
    chat: {
        htmlAttributes: {
            translate: false,
        }
    },
})Let me know if you have questions about this. you guys are the best, thank you!
